Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_max_fanout(25.10)                                    set_max_fanout(25.10)

Name
       set_max_fanout  -  Sets the maximum fanout load limit constraint on the
       specified instance pins, library cell pins,  ports  of  the  top  cell,
       clock waveforms, and/or specified modules

Syntax
       set_max_fanout

       [-help]

       <fanout_limit>

       <object_list>

       [-override]

       Sets the maximum fanout load limit constraint on the specified instance
       pins, library cell pins, ports of the top cell, clock waveforms, and/or
       specified  modules.  When pins of cell instances have their own maximum
       constraint defined in the library, the software will pick the more  ag-
       gressive value of the two.

       When  set  on  a port, the fanout load of the net connected to the port
       must be less than or equal to the specified limit  value  to  meet  the
       constraint.  The fanout load of a net is the sum of the fanout loads of
       the pins driven by the net. When set on a module, the limit applies  to
       all  the  nets of that module. Libraries and library cell pins may also
       have the maximum fanout load limit. In this case the most  constraining
       limit is applied to the nets.

       Use  the report_ports -type fanout_load_limit command to view the maxi-
       mum fanout load limits set on ports of the top cell.

       Fanout load limit can be asserted on input ports, output pins, bidirec-
       tional pins, or ports and library pins. You cannot apply the constraint
       on input pins and output ports.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <fanout_limit>
              Specifies the value of the maximum fanout load limit constraint.
              This is a float number and it must be greater than or  equal  to
              zero.

       <object_><list>
              Specifies a list of objects - input ports, instance output pins,
              designs, or library cell output pins.

       -override
              Overrides  the maximum fanout limit from other sources, such as,
              library or constraints.

              This parameter can be used to force a specific constraint  value
              for  a  specified list of instance pins/port/library cell pins -
              this overrides the maximum/minimum values set prior to this set-
              ting.

              To enable this feature, make the following setting:

              set timing_constraint_enable_drv_limit_override true

Examples
              * The following example sets a maximum fanout load limit of  5.0
                units on all the ports of the top cell:

                set_max_fanout 5.0 [get_ports *]

              * The  following  example  shows  a report of the maximum fanout
                load limit set on ports using the report_ports command:

                set_max_fanout   5.0   [get_ports   *]   report_ports    -type
                fanout_load_limit -pin [get_ports *]

                Example: Maximum Fanout Load Limit Set On Ports Report

                > report_ports -type fanout_load_limit -pin [get_ports *]

                -------------------------------------------

                Pin    Dir  Assertion        Value

                Name

                -------------------------------------------

                CLK2   IN  fanout_load_limit 5.000

                CLK1   IN  fanout_load_limit 5.000

                in2    IN  fanout_load_limit 5.000

                in1    IN  fanout_load_limit 5.000

                -------------------------------------------

